9.0, 1162.7, 1163.1, 1186.1]}, {"text": "from customers in Venezuela. As of December 31, 2015, 26% of our gross trade receivables were from customers in the United", "bbox": [93.9, 1187.7, 1159.8, 1211.1]}, {"text": "States and 14% were from customers in Venezuela. Other than the United States and Venezuela, no other country or single", "bbox": [93.9, 1212.7, 1118.8, 1236.1]}, {"text": "customer accounted for more than 10% of our gross trade receivables at these dates.", "bbox": [93.9, 1237.7, 804.8, 1261.2]}, {"text": "Venezuela. We have continued to experience delays in collecting payments on our receivables from our primary", "bbox": [169.0, 1287.8, 1104.0, 1311.2]}, {"text": "customer in Venezuela. These receivables are not disputed, and we have not historically had material write-offs relating to this", "bbox": [93.9, 1312.8, 1151.5, 1336.2]}, {"text": "customer. Additionally, we routinely monitor the financial stability of our customers. During the second quarter of 2016, we", "bbox": [93.9, 1337.8, 1132.0, 1361.2]}, {"text": "executed a financing agreement with our primary customer in Venezuela in an effort to actively manage these customer", "bbox": [93.9, 1362.8, 1093.6, 1386.2]}, {"text": "receivables, resulting in an exchange of $200 million of outstanding trade receivables for an interest-bearing promissory note.", "bbox": [93.9, 1387.8, 1148.0, 1411.3]}, {"text": "53", "bbox": [618.0, 1561.9, 644.2, 1585.3]}]}